 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Transportation Specialist (Open to both U.S. Citizens and Federal Employees) US Federal Highway Administration Washington, DC Job details Salary $103,690 - $159,286 a year Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Duties 
 Summary 
 The subject position is located in the Office of Transportation Management (HOTM), with approximately equally shared responsibilities within the Office of Transportation Operations (HOTO), both part of the Office of Operations, Federal Highway Administration (FHWA) in Washington, DC. The incumbent serves jointly as a member of the Connected and Automated Vehicles and Emerging Technologies Team and the Manual on Uniform Traffic Control Devices (MUTCD) Team. 
 
 Responsibilities 
 As a Transportation Specialist, you will : 
 
 Provide technically sound oversight, review, coordination, guidance and interpretation to a broad constituency that includes FHWA leadership and field offices, State and local transportation agencies, Congress, the industry and the public. 
 Convert the conclusions of special studies, surveys, and research into regulations, policies, and guidance for traffic control devices and automated vehicle integration with roadways systems. 
 Identify and recommend research initiatives to advance the state of the practice with respect to traffic control device technologies and applications as well as to facilitate the safe integration of automated vehicles within United States (US) roadways. 
 Serve as the Contracting Officerâ€™s Technical Representative, providing technical oversight and project control and accountability. He/she prepares statements of work, reviews proposals, and ensures that contractor deliverables meet the contract requirements. 
 Provide fiscal accountability, through the monitoring and control of resource allocations and the conduct of project and program reviews. He/she develops the overall vision, strategic goals and objectives, and annual performance plans and roadmaps for assigned program areas. 
 
 The  ideal candidate for this position  is a mid-career or senior Transportation Specialist with expertise related to traffic control devices and strategies and or and/or new and emerging highway transportation operations capabilities. Examples of emerging highway transportation operations include connected vehicles, automated driving systems, machine-learning and artificial intelligence in transportation applications, or wireless and wireline communications supporting highway transportation applications. The ideal candidate will also have numerous experiences leading coordination with multiple organizations to achieve transportation safety and/or operations goals. 
